Name: bladder benign neoplasm
Definition: A urinary system benign neoplasm located_in the bladder including papillomas
Synonym: squamous cell carcinoma of paranasal sinus

Name: ureteral benign neoplasm
Definition: A neuropathy that is characterized by damage to a single nerve

Name: renal adenoma
Definition: A muscle benign neoplasm that is characterized as benign hyperplastic lesions of uterine smooth muscle cells.

Name: kidney benign neoplasm
Definition: A cystadenocarcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells originating in glandular tissue forming serous lesions.

Name: urinary tract papillary transitional cell benign neoplasm
Definition: An ovarian disease where ovaries do not produce estrogen despite high levels of circulating gonadotropins in women under 40.
